- Updated: 2026-03-11T15:27:44Z # [Bug] Kimi k2p5 tool calls silently dropped in Feishu channel (v2026.3.8)

## Environment - **OpenClaw version**: 2026.3.8 (3caab92)
- **Channel**: Feishu (WebSocket mode)
- **Model**: kimi-coding/k2p5 - **API type**: anthropic-messages
- **Platform**: macOS (Darwin 25.3.0) ## Problem Description Tool calls from Kimi k2p5 model are not executed when using the Feishu channel. The model generates tool calls correctly, but OpenClaw returns the tool call XML directly to the user as text instead of executing the tools. ## Reproduction Steps

1. Configure Kimi k2p5 model: ```json
